<!--
  CropperScreenshotDemo.rozie — content-STABLE screenshot consumer for the
  Cropper wrapper (the cropper-VR-determinism cell).

  Where CropperDemo.rozie is the BEHAVIORAL two-way-data + handle cell, THIS demo
  is the SEPARATE deterministic SCREENSHOT cell — never extend it for behavior,
  and never bolt pixels onto the behavioral one.

  Determinism levers:
    1. :src is a self-contained SVG data URL (network-free, identical in Docker).
    2. A FIXED :data crop box ({ x, y, width, height } + identity transform),
       applied in the wrapper's `ready` callback — in IMAGE coordinates.
    3. An EXPLICIT pixel size on the wrapper root via consumer `style`
       fallthrough (320×240, the image's intrinsic size). This is the CRITICAL
       D-10 lever: Cropper sizes its canvas + crop box relative to the CONTAINER,
       so the same image-coord box only lands at the same SCREEN pixels if the
       container is byte-identically sized across all 6 targets. Left content-
       sized (the wrapper's default max-width:100%, no height), each framework's
       wrapper DOM measures a hair differently → the box drifts → D-10 fails.
       Pinning the container to the image's exact intrinsic box removes all
       letterboxing ambiguity.
    4. :guides / :center / :background left at defaults (deterministic chrome).
    5. :responsive false — no resize re-render races.

  One .rozie source compiles to six per-framework screenshot consumers; the Linux
  PNG baseline is generated by the orchestrator in pinned Linux Docker (NOT here —
  macOS baselines are forbidden, feedback_vr_linux_baselines). Until it lands the
  matrix cell auto-fixmes on baselineExists().
-->

<rozie name="CropperScreenshotDemo">

<components>
{
  Cropper: '../../packages/ui/cropper/src/Cropper.rozie',
}
</components>

<script>
import 'cropperjs/dist/cropper.css'

const SAMPLE = 'data:image/svg+xml;base64,'

// A FIXED crop box (applied in the wrapper's ready callback) — deterministic
// pixels for the box, modal overlay, and view box.
const FIXED_BOX = { x: 60, y: 40, width: 180, height: 160, rotate: 0, scaleX: 1, scaleY: 1 }
</script>

<template>
<div class="cropper-screenshot-demo">
  <Cropper
    style="width: 320px; height: 240px;"
    :src="SAMPLE"
    :data="FIXED_BOX"
    :view-mode="1"
    :responsive="false"
  />
</div>
</template>

<style>
.cropper-screenshot-demo {
  padding: 12px;
  background: #ffffff;
}
</style>

</rozie>
